label: [Exp] Status Ticker - take 2 - Client Code
info: ::: aim Create a ticker wall using the status colours. This is an experimental flow showing off the flexibility of Node-RED. The flows usage is limited to optics. ::: ### WARNING This flow, once started does not stop!!! The only way to stop the flow is to use the "Restart Flows" menu point on the Deploy drop-down. ![img](https://cdn.openmindmap.org/content/1691070147870_Screen_Shot_2023-08-03_at_15.41.00.png) ### Flow Explanation The flow consists of 16 by 16 instances of the LED subflow. The LED subflow contains the logic for setting the status colours. Each node in the flow becomes a message with a `column` and `row` value. The column number is incremented as the message is passed through the nodes while the row value is set at the beginning of each row. Messages are looped within a row by link-out and link-in pair at the beginning and end of each row. Becuause the flow uses no state information, it is difficult to assign each node a fixed column number (the node would need to store that). ### Inputs There are three actions: - Random button to make status blink randomly - Rolling button that makes status colours roll through the colour ranges - DotMatrix that will produce a dot matrix text There are two other settings: - verbose which will add a status text with the row and column number of the node. - freeze which will freeze the status after the initial display. ### Tooling - [Dot Matrix Tool](http://dotmatrixtool.com) for generating the text matrix. The configuration to use is `16px by 16px, column major, big endian.` - the result needs to be placed in the subflows' function node. ### Preview ![img](https://cdn.openmindmap.org/content/1698426075545_status_ticker_2.gif)
